Vice President Mike Pence delivered a speech at the Latino Coalition's "Make Small Business Great Again Policy Summit" in Washington, D.C. He expressed his appreciation for the Latino Coalition and praised the contributions of Hispanic-owned businesses to the American economy. Pence also discussed President Trump's plans to repeal and replace Obamacare, cut taxes, roll back regulations, and invest in infrastructure. He emphasized the importance of a merit-based society and the rule of law, and promised to work with the Hispanic community to achieve real and positive immigration reform. Pence concluded by sharing his personal story as the grandson of an immigrant and expressing his commitment to keeping the American Dream alive.